This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it presents a Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) based sequence model for extractive summarization of documents. It may also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) because summarization is a common task in this field. Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the model, which could fall under Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions abstractive training, which involves generating new text, and could be related to Neural Networks (cs.NE).
